none: This first collection of sijo by Cho Un (1898- ) contains mostly the ones written during the Japanese colonial period. Cho was a participant of the Chosŏn Munhakka Tongmaeng who fled to North Korea. A famous newspaper illustrator Yi Sŭng-man drew the book cover and a famous sijo poet Yi Pyŏng-gi (1891-1968) designed the typography of the book title.
